The paper discusses the application of an anytime heuristic search algorithm for incomplete information games, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the strategy fusion and non-locality problems, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of natural evolution (cs.NE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
